      "section_id": "MPS-0201",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "The paper begins from a bounded organizational-learning proposition: firm-specific capability may be represented partly by relationships among factual context, selected action, rationale, escalation, and outcome rather than by documents alone. This project calls that representation a professional interaction graph. Organizational research and the observed workflow structures make the construct analytically useful, yet they do not establish that every firm possesses a unique ontology, that the construct is legally protectable, or that an external model can learn it with commercially meaningful fidelity.",
