      "section_id": "MPS-0202",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "The causal mechanism requires a complete source-to-sink chain: professional asset, read authority, transformation, transmission, destination, retention, secondary use, and customer consent or control. The repository confirms several possible boundary components, including remote MCP declarations and hosted skill or instruction upload. It does not establish credentials, actual traffic, provider-side retention, evaluation use, generalized training, or cross-tenant normalization. Missing retention and secondary-use links prevent a covert-capture finding, although they do not eliminate privacy, privilege, dependency, or architectural-risk questions.",
