      "section_id": "MPS-0203",
      "selector": {
        "exact": "The proposed sector externality is conditional on overlap, transferability, legal permission, technical reuse, and downstream substitution. Under those assumptions, multiple firms could contribute traces that improve a generalized upstream capability even where no single contribution is decisive. The hypothesis is consistent with organizational-learning and competition-policy pathways, but current evidence does not measure cross-firm overlap, marginal learning value, substitutability, market effect, or provider conduct. A valid test requires exposure measurements and a benchmark that isolates value beyond public legal materials.",
