      "selector": {
        "exact": "The normative conclusion is intentionally narrower than the causal hypothesis. Regardless of whether sector-level reuse is occurring, firms have a defensible reason to preserve independent control over professional interaction graphs, derivatives, telemetry, evaluation, portability, and termination. The recommendation is testable: controls should reduce observable exposure, improve provenance and auditability, preserve deletion and export rights, and make switching credible. Controls that cannot demonstrate those outcomes may become expensive security theater rather than effective institutional governance.",
